00:00:08.600 --> 00:00:13.539
Now we've all seen those great pictures of athlete's frozen in motion - the 'Decisive Moment'.

00:00:13.600 --> 00:00:18.950
But how do the photographers get those pictures? I often get asked what 
my settings are when I am looking

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:20.810
to freeze action, but you know,

00:00:20.900 --> 00:00:24.410
there's no simple answer.

00:00:24.500 --> 00:00:27.390
AdoramaTV presents

00:00:27.400 --> 00:00:34.390
Stay Focused with Doug McKinlay.

00:00:36.090 --> 00:00:39.059
There's no magic answer when it comes to
shutter speed for stop action photography

00:00:39.100 --> 00:00:42.739
There is constantly changing variables, could be the light,

00:00:42.739 --> 00:00:46.540
the angle of the light, subjects speed, the lens you're using.

00:00:46.540 --> 00:00:50.059
So it's up to the photographer to make a
decision on the spot

00:00:50.059 --> 00:00:56.440
for each situation. Of course, shutter speeds are the key component for great

00:00:56.440 --> 00:00:57.159
stop action pictures.

00:00:57.159 --> 00:01:01.250
On bright sunny days you are going to get really fast shutter speeds and lower ISO's.

00:01:01.250 --> 00:01:04.690
Cloudier days may be slower shutter speeds augmented with 

00:01:04.690 --> 00:01:09.049
high ISO's. Now each photographer is going to have to make their own decision

00:01:09.049 --> 00:01:12.340
given the light situation they're in but
as a rule of thumb

00:01:12.340 --> 00:01:15.390
1/250th of a second is enough to stop action

00:01:15.390 --> 00:01:19.140
if it's coming across the front of the lens.

00:01:19.140 --> 00:01:22.710
1/60th however can stop action with the subject coming
toward you but either way

00:01:22.710 --> 00:01:26.900
I always set my camera to shutter priority,
that way I know I have complete control

00:01:26.900 --> 00:01:28.150
over the shutter speeds.

00:01:28.150 --> 00:01:31.470
Now focal length of the lens is important too.

00:01:31.470 --> 00:01:34.710
Currently I'm using this: 70 - 200mm 2.8.

00:01:34.710 --> 00:01:37.939
The reason being is I can isolate my
subject

00:01:37.939 --> 00:01:41.060
from the background I'm not too
concerned about the backgrounds here, I'm more

00:01:41.060 --> 00:01:42.869
concerned about the action in my subject

00:01:42.869 --> 00:01:49.869
The longer lens allow me to really
really get tight.

